node.text:
At Meow Wolf Denver, was created by @volarduran and David Ocelotl Garcia. It’s an exploration and physical manifestation of energy, sculpture, color and light using a technique David developed called Abstract Imaginism.

Opening Fall 2021

🎥: @valentinovalentin

🎥: @jilannspitzmiller @magicisrealism 

Starring: @emilyamontoya @mondoqiwah @csg_nm @shaktihowethart @astral_weaves 

🎵: @davidlast

node.text:
@shrineon is a brilliant artist and activist who's incorporating his iconic trash art motifs in the form of a mural for @omegamartusa. His work has transcended into a healing method, which is so crucial nowadays. Working with him has been an absolute dream and we can't wait to see his finished mural for Omega Mart.

Directed, Written and Edited by @jilannspitzmiller 
Produced by Isabel Zermani (@magicisrealism)
Cinematography by Morgan Capps, @alupovich and Jilann Spitzmiller
Additional Cinematography courtesy of @thegreatoven by Archie Thomas
@archiethomasdotcom and James Gomez Thompson @j_gomez_thompson
Music: “Below the Sun” by Skygaze

Special thanks to James Thompson & Joe Adamsdale of Great Oven

node.text:
Do you miss going to the movies? We partnered with @denverdigerati to showcase 20 minutes of insane digital pieces to be shown at @convergencestation - how will they be shown? You’ll have to wait and see on September 17th…

Featuring: John Butler, Jake Fried, Heather Crank, Milton Croissant III, Cassie Shao, Cyane Tornatzky, Jeremy Couillard, Raquel Meyers and Eli Ayers.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Meow Wolf on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Wheelchair Space Kitchen by @wheelchairsportscamp and @greggsdrumparty is inspired by the disability advocates and protesters from the 1970s who broke out of the nursing home and fought hard for access to public transportation and community living - making Denver the first city to have accessible public transit and one of the first places disabled people could live outside of institutions. The room pays respect to the intersection of disability history and the future of disability justice. This room is also heavily influenced by the DIY spirit of adapting spaces to live and create as a means of survival. 

📸: @katerussellphoto @kennedycottrell
